Create all the methods in one class
   Then Access the methods you want by creating an object reference 
       So whenever you do, it's allocating a memory for all the varaibles 
       
       
       
   Generating a Random Email Address or Username?
        
        int ran;
    	ran = 100 + (int)(Math.random() * ((10000 - 100) + 1));
    	Entering the email address will look like this:
    	driver.findElement(By.id("Email")).sendKeys("signuptest" + ran + "@test.com");